@justinmk would you mind taking another look? I've updated `util.root_pattern` as discussed.

Previously, the function did this:
```
for each parent directory:
    for each pattern:
        if match:
            return match
```

I have switched the two loops around so that it now does the following:
```
for each pattern:
    for each parent directory:
        if match:
            return match
```

There is a slight performance hit because instead of traversing parent directories once, it now traverses parent directories `n` times for `n` patterns.

On the plus side though this resolves the issue not only for `csharp_ls`, but also for a whole bunch of other language servers which use a similar pattern of doing `return util.root_pattern("pattern1")(path) or util.root_pattern("pattern2")(path) or ...`. Some examples:

- [omnisharp](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/90a28fd7637b66e055af62387ecee06f7cbd3173/lua/lspconfig/server_configurations/omnisharp.lua#L41-L49)
- [tsserver](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/90a28fd7637b66e055af62387ecee06f7cbd3173/lua/lspconfig/server_configurations/tsserver.lua#L15-L18)
- [cairo_ls](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/90a28fd7637b66e055af62387ecee06f7cbd3173/lua/lspconfig/server_configurations/cairo_ls.lua#L11-L14)
- [hls](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/90a28fd7637b66e055af62387ecee06f7cbd3173/lua/lspconfig/server_configurations/hls.lua#L8-L12)
